==English==
===Etymology===
New Latin, from Greek ζῷον.  Coined by Bose in 1802
===Variant spelling===
[[zoœa]]
===Noun===
'''zoëa'''
#''(Zoölogy):'' A peculiar larval stage of certain decapod [[Crustacea]], especially of crabs and certain [[Anomura]], originally thought to be from a distinct genus.  Also called the [[copepod]] stage.

===Notes===
*In this stage the anterior part of the body is relatively large, and usually bears three or four long spines. The years are conspicuous, and the antennæ and jaws are long, fringed organs used in swimming. The thoracic legs are undeveloped or rudimentary, the abdomen long, slender, and often without appendages. The zoëa, after casting its shell, changes to a [[megalop]]s.

